    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>A great compact way, without having to use a third party library, would be to <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/57318525/10749567\">use the ternary operator (?:) as described by @BasilBourque</a>:</p>\n<pre><code>s = s.length() &gt; 10 ? s.substring(0, 10 - 2).concat(&quot;..&quot;) : s;\n</code></pre>\n<p>but it might be just as simple to use a &quot;one-line&quot; if-statement:</p>\n<pre><code>if (s.length() &gt; 10) s = s.substring(0, 10 - 2) + &quot;..&quot;;\n</code></pre>\n"
